  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Evaluate the role of iNO in early ischemia reperfusion injury in marginal liver grafts during human orthotopic liver or liver/kidney transplantation.</measure>
    <time_frame>24 hours to 1 month</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>iNO group will show accelerated restoration of liver allograft function following liver transplantation and this may translate to better clinical outcomes. Marginal grafts may function better in the treated group</measure>
    <time_frame>1 month to 1 year</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
